# This installs some ELF 64-bit libraries in /usr/lib/
# that might cause problems if anything requires xmms2 libraries

# Not certain how to do a DESTDIR type install with this


#            'libvorbis::--disable-vorbis:to play ogg vorbis files' )

with version stable 0.8DrO_o 0.6DrMattDestruction 0.5DrLecter 0.4DrKosmos 0.2DrJekyll 0.2DrHouse
with base    curl faad2 libao libmad libmpcdec libvorbis sqlite
#with base    curl faad2 libao libcdio libmad libmpcdec libvorbis sqlite
# libofa not hosted for download anywhere?
#with base    curl faad2 libao libcdio libmad libmpcdec libofa libvorbis sqlite
with elect   SDL_ttf  '' ''             for SDL visualization client
with elect   alsa-lib '' --disable-alsa for alsa sound support
with elect   ffmpeg   '' ''             for support for several audio and video codecs
with elect   jackit   '' ''             for jack sound server support
with role    audio/network audio/player
with trait   gnome
with trait   broke
with source  $SOURCEFORGE_URL xmms2/xmms2/0.8%20DrO_o/xmms2-$VERSION.tar.bz2
with info    omit 20130101
with info    last 20111020
with info    home http://wiki.xmms2.xmms.se/index.php/Main_Page
with info    cite 'redesigned xmms music player
It features a client-server model, allowing multiple
(even simultaneous!) user interfaces, both textual and graphical.
All common audio formats are supported using plugins.
On top of this, there is a flexible media library to organize your music.
See the features page for more details.'

build(){
./waf configure --prefix /usr &&
./waf build &&
./waf install "--destdir=$DESTDIR"
}
